# AI Governance Controls (10 GOV)

MedinovAI AI governance framework. All AI/ML components must align with these controls.

## GOV-01: Model Risk Register

- Every model must be registered with risk class, owner, and lineage.
- Track: purpose, data sources, performance baselines, approval status.

## GOV-02: Pre-Deployment Validation

- Mandatory validation pipeline before any model deployment.
- Include: unit tests, integration tests, performance benchmarks, security scan.
- Block deployment on failure.

## GOV-03: Bias Testing

- Test across demographics and subgroups.
- Document fairness metrics; flag disparities above defined thresholds.
- No deployment without bias assessment.

## GOV-04: Human Override Pathways

- Clear override mechanism for AI decisions affecting patients or safety.
- Audit trail for overrides; qualified person sign-off where required.
- Overrides must be reversible and traceable.

## GOV-05: Explainability Standards

- Explainability requirements scaled by risk class.
- High-risk: feature importance, decision rationale, confidence bounds.
- Audit-ready; reproducible explanations on demand.

## GOV-06: Performance Monitoring

- Continuous monitoring of accuracy, latency, drift.
- Alerts on degradation; automated rollback where configured.
- Dashboard and periodic review cadence.

## GOV-07: Data Lineage Tracking

- Trace data from source through model to prediction.
- Support impact analysis and regulatory inquiry.
- Version datasets, features, and models together.

## GOV-08: Vendor Accountability

- Contracts must specify AI/ML SLAs, security, and compliance.
- Vendor models require same governance as internal models.
- Periodic vendor assessment and documentation.

## GOV-09: Incident Response

- Defined process for AI incidents: detection, containment, remediation.
- Root cause analysis; update model and controls as needed.
- Report per regulatory and internal policy.

## GOV-10: Cross-Functional Oversight

- Model governance committee with clinical, legal, compliance, engineering.
- Regular review of model inventory, incidents, and controls.
- Escalation path for high-risk decisions.
